      • findHeader

        private void findHeader(ParsableByteArray source)
        Attempts to locate the start of the next frame header.

        If a frame header is located then the state is changed to STATE_READING_HEADER, the first two bytes of the header are written into headerScratch, and the position of the source is advanced to the byte that immediately follows these two bytes.

        If a frame header is not located then the position of the source is advanced to the limit, and the method should be called again with the next source to continue the search.

        Parameters:
        source - The source from which to read.

      • readHeaderRemainder

        private void readHeaderRemainder(ParsableByteArray source)
        Attempts to read the remaining two bytes of the frame header.

        If a frame header is read in full then the state is changed to STATE_READING_FRAME, the media format is output if this has not previously occurred, the four header bytes are output as sample data, and the position of the source is advanced to the byte that immediately follows the header.

        If a frame header is read in full but cannot be parsed then the state is changed to STATE_READING_HEADER.

        If a frame header is not read in full then the position of the source is advanced to the limit, and the method should be called again with the next source to continue the read.

        Parameters:
        source - The source from which to read.

      • readFrameRemainder

        private void readFrameRemainder(ParsableByteArray source)
        Attempts to read the remainder of the frame.

        If a frame is read in full then true is returned. The frame will have been output, and the position of the source will have been advanced to the byte that immediately follows the end of the frame.

        If a frame is not read in full then the position of the source will have been advanced to the limit, and the method should be called again with the next source to continue the read.

        Parameters:
        source - The source from which to read.
